Big Sharks on Balloons!

First video is up of our Do it yourself Florida Road Trip.  We hauled the @alumacraftboats down to the ocean and some of the most epic memories of my life went down. 

This first video we stopped near Stuart to visit my buddy @blacktiph. 

Link is in my bio-

Wow what an absolute blast-Giant Jacks on top water is nuts! 

We timed it perfectly this week here in the Florida Keys.  Brought my own boat down and saw the show going down with massive Giant jacks busting on baits up shallow at ridiculous fast speeds…we chased them down and all hell broke loose something you must do and see if your a freshwater guy or gal. 

We’ve been catching so many different species here.. 30+ Tarpon 10+ Permit Mutton Snapper, Yellow Tail Snapper, Grouper, Snook, Yellow Jacks, HoundFish, Mahi Mahi, Mangroove Snapper, Pompano , Sharks… and so many other fish.  All on our spoons or plastics.

Some of the most explosive strikes and hard fighting fish to catch.  Every time I bring my boat down to the ocean I learn so much.  Bringing untraditional methods that work well in freshwater also work exceptionally well in saltwater.

Working on editing some incredible footage we have of some many different fish species on 2 main baits.  Jigging spoons and jig and plastic. 

Every bait shop in town up and down the coast will tell this….

“Get some bait- shrimp or Pelchers, anchor up and chum and fish. 

I know this works great but we rarely chum unless we fish snapper or sharks and have tremendous success with our @haatfishing jigging spoons.  But yet very very few people are using them or are using Livescope. 
So if you decide to ever try these spoons out make sure you upgrade Your Gamakatsu hooks to a 2X EWG #4 and #6 2X EWG and Add our U/V tape and up grade split rings but you won’t need to buy $50.00 or more of bait and chum per day…

I’ve spent the last 10 years fishing different areas from Tampa- Everglades- Marco island, Stuart, Fort Pierce, and the Florida Keys.

And without a doubt from shore or a boat the Florida Keys is the best and easiest salt water fishing I’ve ever had.  The option of fishing The Gulf Stream and Atlantic Ocean on one side of the road and the Gulf side on the other is like no other place I’ve fished.  So put this place on your bucket list the Florida Keys we are renting a place in Marathon.

Biggest Brown of the season for our crew came this Saturday customers had an epic day with some giants caught and released.  Big shout out to my my crew @fowlcal @rob_graef @wisco_pinner who consistently put our customers on sone of the biggest browns in the world through the ice. Great work guys!👊

We use our custom @haatfishing 40” medium that works Perfect for jigging or in the jaw Jackers.

Not sure what these warm temps are going to do to the ice but we are checking it daily.  In the meantime steelhead fishing was great today in the river and soon we will be back in the boat casting and jigging for browns.  Very happy that this warm weather followed us back from Florida 😜.

If your looking to have a blast jigging Lake Trout and want some exceptional scenery head up to Northern Michigan on Lake Superior.  We just got back from the Porcupine Mountains in Silver City Michigan.  Check out the link in my bio such a cool way to catch them! 

#lakesuperior #laketrout #jigging

Finally got it done shot our #2 buck “Alto”. @fowlcal got us permission to hunt this property so big thanks Cal!  Early  last week Cal missed our #1 buck we call Tines because of his tall brow tines he’s 170-180 class 6 1/2 year old we’ve hunted the last 3 years and finally had a crack at him.  So the highs and lows are brutal at times.

What was most important to me was I was able to hunt this deer how I wanted to.  I was hunting a big Marsh where there’s not many options for tree stands and definitely not for the wind we had.  So I snuck in so slow which took forever but was down wind didn’t blow any deer out because there was a solid 10-15 mph wind. 

Got settled down around a fallen tree and tree trunk on the ground.  And had this dream of always wanted to kill a big buck on the ground and I did on my dads birthday. 

I saw this deer about an hour earlier chasing a doe a 1/2 mile south of me and running south so I figured we’ll at least I see him and where he’s at now.  But 45 minutes later I got a picture on my cell camera running directly north and got ready.  5 minutes later a big doe come running in stops 15 yards to my right and looks behind her and boom there he is at 20 yards appearing in the big gaps in the swap marsh grass.  The doe runs right by me behind me in the opening and I knew he was going to follow her.  And he stepped out broadside 20 yards and walking directly at the doe and I smoked him.  He ran 30 yards stopped got tipsey and fell over.  It was awesome that Cal got to be there for the recovery.  Very blessed and grateful for this opportunity to harvest such a special animal! 

#bbd #whitetail #bowhunting #deerseason #bowhunter

I want to take a minute to thank all of the current and former  EMT's,Firefighters, and police. 

These folks put their lives on the line for us everyday.  My daughter @hanna_haataja is a EMT and it's definitely frustrating for me a parent to know she's getting $13.00 per hour and volunteer firefighters make nothing.  While folks are hiring at McDonald's and the local gas station for 17-18 per hour.  How does this even happen? I mean is there something we can do to change this? 

They are going to run into fires, see horrific accidents, shootings, stabbings, and death. 

A very traumatic job to say the least.  So I'd like to really once again Thank all you first responders for doing what you do!
